## Question

**Fat** asked on 20 Jun 2024

Hello everyone, After upgrading to the newest Telerik Blazor UI version (6.0.2), which includes the new spreadsheet component, I've been experiencing issues when trying to open and use the spreadsheet. I've been working for quite some time now to fix this issue, but it also doesn't seem that other people have mentioned my specific problem. So, I am posting here in hopes that it might help somebody in the future when encountering the same problem. The error is triggered whenever the spreadsheet is opened. ### Response

**Dimo** commented on 24 Jun 2024

@FateEscape Recently another customer said this problem was caused by using outdated Telerik localization.resx files. Please make sure yours are up-to-date. Other than that, we haven't reproduced such an error. On a side note, please ask the license holder at your company to assign you an active Telerik license. This will make your Telerik account: compliant with our license agreement eligible to receive technical support from us
